title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: UNICEF’s communication and advocacy efforts reachedaround 750,000 people monthlywith evidence-based messages through social media, website and offline activities. UNICEF’s Risk Communication and Community Engagement activities contributed to an increased acceptability of COVID-19 protection measures and vaccination as confirmed by the WHO-UNICEF BI study. UNICEF also advocated for reducing the digital divide, helping to position access to the internet;on public and policy agendas and integrate a new vision for school computer labs into Government standards. Using multiple platforms and diverse activities, UNICEF advocated for safe reopening of schools which contributed to the opening of all schools in October. ; | Status:Met | As-of Date:21/12/2021
